Saint Pierce is a small town full of sinners. Heaven help me resist the temptation of Devereaux Huxley. 

When I round the corner, I come face to face with the dangerous man invading my thoughts.

He’s enjoying a cigarette, resting his back against the concrete of the building. His whiskey-colored gaze slides over to me and a lazy smile lifts one corner of his mouth.

“I wasn’t expecting you,” I say.

Devereaux takes a long pull of the cigarette and blows the smoke out in rings, his sultry lips mesmerizing me. “No one ever is. Expect the unexpected with me.” 

He looks like the devil in his tailored black suit, ready to bargain for my soul. And the way his eyes ravage my body…makes me want to barter.
